The Club is delighted to confirm the signing of Bobby Decordova-Reid on loan from Cardiff City, subject to domestic and international clearance.
The 26-year-old forward will remain at Craven Cottage for the duration of the season, in a deal that could later become permanent.
Decordova-Reid last played in the Championship in 2017/18 when he netted 19 league goals and was named in the PFA Team of the Year.

The Club is delighted to announce the signing of midfielder Harrison Reed from Southampton, subject to clearance.
Reed joins Fulham on a season-long loan deal, which could be made permanent at a later date.

We are delighted to confirm the permanent signing of Josh Onomah from Tottenham Hotspur.
The 22-year-old arrives at Fulham as part of the deal that has seen Ryan Sessegnon join Spurs.
Onomah has agreed a three-year contract, with a Club option for a further 12 months, keeping him in SW6 until at least the summer of 2022.

We can confirm that Ryan Sessegnon has joined Tottenham Hotspur for an undisclosed fee.
The deal is a record sale for Fulham, and also sees midfielder Josh Onomah move to Craven Cottage.

text:
Win the chance to step onto the Cottage turf at this Saturday’s game and win with Coral! Simply tell us what happened next when Fulham defeated Huddersfield Town 2-0 in 2015? 18+, must have a match ticket to FFC v Huddersfield Town.
A) Seko Fofana runs the length of the pitch and squares it to Ryan Tunnicliffe for a simple tap in, sending the travelling fans into raptures.
B) Seko Fofana runs the length of the pitch and sees his shot hit the post and bounce to safety.
C) Seko Fofana runs the length of the pitch, cannons a shot off the post but is on hand to slide it home on the rebound, sending the #FFC fans into raptures.
Good Luck!
